    "text": "The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. APJAKTU NSS CELL Units 184, 338, 559 & 628 of College of Engineering Chengannur successfully conducted SPANDANAM – a blood donation camp. Over 60 volunteers participated in this noble cause. The annual sports meet of the College of Engineering Chengannur. SIGHT Gramina Digital Hub is an IEEE SIGHT/HAC Funded Project with a project funding of $4000 in which a digital hub was successfully set up in Kulanada Grama Panchyat. After the successful completion of the project, the IEEE SIGHT Chengannur College of Engineering has established a village-level digital hub in Kulanada Punnakunnu Scheduled Caste (SC) […] The NSS unit of CEC banded together to build a home in a swift manner for their homeless classmate. IGNITE is a two-year technical outreach program initiated and organized by the IEEE Student Branch, College of Engineering, Chengannur (CEC) as an extension of the WIE STAR Program for the students of secondary schools. Aswin Mohan of College of Engineering, Chengannur developed an app to coordinate the services provided to people who are under observation at homes with COVID-19 symptoms. SUMMIT’19, the biennial techno-cultural fest of College of Engineering Chengannur.",
