    "section": "MAKER STATION",
    "text": "The post FORCEGO appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . ” FORCEGO ” is developed using the powerful Python language, incorporates advanced features such as Text-to-Speech (TTS), Google Text-to-Speech (gTTS), and Text Recognition features. These groundbreaking technologies work harmoniously to provide a seamless and inclusive experience, enabling the app to read out texts from various sources, including PDFs and images, in the user’s native language. Also ” ForceGo ” becomes the first-ever application to offer real-time translation into Malayalam language. With its user friendly graphical user interface , FORCEGO analyze and extract text from images, enabling visually impaired individuals to access content that was previously inaccessible. The post FORCEGO appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post SUMMER INTERNSHIP PROGRAM appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The 5-day internship program at the College of Engineering Chengannur! This program is designed to inspire and motivate higher secondary students to pursue novel ideas and explore technological possibilities outside the scope of their usual academic curriculum through project-based learning. Our goal is to provide students with hands-on experience with real projects that will help them prepare for college and develop valuable technical skills. Through this program, students will have the opportunity to expand their technical expertise and delve into the endless possibilities of science, technology, and social development. Our one-of-a-kind internship will allow students to earn while they learn and develop practical skills that can benefit them in the future. By participating in this program, students will be aligning themselves with the “Digital India, the power to empower” philosophy of using digital technology to empower individuals. Our challenging and informative internship provides a rewarding experience that fosters learning and personal growth. If you have a passion for technology, this is the perfect opportunity to explore your interests and expand your horizons. Program Objectives: Motivate youth to discover and nurture the creative side hidden in them. Help youth in choosing their careers. To inspire students with hands-on experience in emerging technologies. Encourage youth to be more productive. Enable students to earn income and gain practical work experience during their learning The post SUMMER INTERNSHIP PROGRAM appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post MAKER STATION appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The Maker Station, an innovative and exciting program organized by Tinkerhub Foundation in partnership with Amazon India, which is an iteration of our popular program, Learning Stations. We are excited to share that the College of Engineering, Chengannur has been selected as one of the venue.Tinkerhub CE Chengannur in collaboration with the Training and Placement Cell of the College of Engineering Chengannur has acted as the venue organisers. This was an opportunity to be a part of one of the largest learning programs in the state which brings together students and makers from various backgrounds to showcase their creativity, skills, and passion for technology. The post MAKER STATION appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post SPANDANAM – Blood Donation Camp appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post SPANDANAM – Blood Donation Camp appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post IHRD THARANG 2023 appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . IHRD Tharang’23, the first National Level Techno-Cultural-Entrepreneurial event organized by the Institute of Human Resources Development (IHRD). Adhering to the theme YOUTH, SCIENCE and LEADERSHIP, IHRD Tharang’23 aims at providing a holistic experience to the students and empower them in building ideas to design models and finished products in technology, cultural and entrepreneurship domains. The tech fest will be held in College of Engineering, Chengannur on February 3rd , 4th , 5th 2023 and job fair on 6th of February. Over the span of 6 days, i.e. from 2nd February, 2023 with inauguration, three days of tech fest from 3rd February to 5th February and job fair on 6th February there will be an overall participation of about 60,000 people for IHRD Tharang’23. IHRD Tharang’23 will have compulsory participation from all 87 institutions of IHRD across the 14 districts of Kerala, which comprises of 9 engineering colleges, 8 polytechnic colleges, 45 applied science colleges, 15 technical higher secondary schools, 2 model finishing schools and 8 Regional/Extension/Study Centres. Participants of IHRD Thrang’23 will have the opportunity to choose from about 25+ workshops, 30+ competitions designed for various students’ levels and aptitude along with about 85 stalls to visit for. The stalls are separated out to different purpose stalls such as for school and college project expos, 10+ government institution stalls such as that of K-DISC, Kerala Excise Department, Fire force, VSSC, Naval NCC etc. Artistic gallery stalls, AR/VR zones would also be a part of event attraction for IHRD Tharang’23. Along with the participation from the institutions, with our cultural programs being open to all, we",
