  {
    "id": "8409bc030f465e85",
    "source": "page",
    "url": "https://ceconline.edu/feed",
    "title": "College of Engineering Chengannur",
    "section": "MAKER STATION",
    "text": "Regional/Extension/Study Centres. Participants of IHRD Thrang’23 will have the opportunity to choose from about 25+ workshops, 30+ competitions designed for various students’ levels and aptitude along with about 85 stalls to visit for. The stalls are separated out to different purpose stalls such as for school and college project expos, 10+ government institution stalls such as that of K-DISC, Kerala Excise Department, Fire force, VSSC, Naval NCC etc. Artistic gallery stalls, AR/VR zones would also be a part of event attraction for IHRD Tharang’23. Along with the participation from the institutions, with our cultural programs being open to all, we also expect a participation of around 3000 people from public who would attend the cultural programs arranged on 2nd , 3rd , 4th and 5th of February by celebrities like Jassie Gift, Navya Nair, Sithara Krishnakumar, Pradeep Somasundaran and Rasmi Satheesh. Cumulating a variety of events to cater the taste of a wide community, IHRD Tharang’23 is a one-stop destination for knowledge, fun and entertainment. The post IHRD THARANG 2023 appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post SIGHT Gramina Digital Hub appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . After the successful completion of the project, the IEEE SIGHT Chengannur College of Engineering has established a village-level digital hub in Kulanada Punnakunnu Scheduled Caste (SC) Colony. The hub now serves as a centralized location providing appropriate solutions for the socially relevant issues identified in the area. With the support of the local community and the Pandalam block Panchayat, a previously non-functional building has been transformed into a fully functional hub. The digital hub is equipped with a solar electrification system, ensuring uninterrupted power supply to meet the needs of the community. A state-of-the-art smart classroom has been installed, allowing students to access online education resources and keep up with their studies. Additionally, a well-stocked library has been established, providing residents with a wide range of books and educational materials. The hub also features emergency health and sanitation facilities, ensuring the well-being of the community members. Proper waste management systems have been implemented, promoting cleanliness and hygiene within the area. The completion of the project has led to an increase in standards of living within the marginalized community of Kulanada Grama Panchayat, ward number 8. The residents now have access to digital literacy programs, empowering them with the necessary skills to navigate the digital world. Skill development programs and counseling sessions are regularly conducted, enhancing the employability and well-being of the community members. Overall, the project has successfully mitigated poverty and paved the way for a sustainable future for the marginalized community. The digital hub serves as a catalyst for positive change, uplifting the residents of Kulanada Punnakunnu Scheduled Caste Colony and creating opportunities for a better life. The post SIGHT Gramina Digital Hub appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post Sahapadikkoru Veedu 🏠: CEC Flood Relief Activity appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . With the flood of 2019 having taken its toll on the state, many were left homeless and hopeless. As a way to alleviate the ramifications of the flood, the NSS unit of CEC banded together to build a home in a swift manner for their homeless classmate. The coordination of the students were apparent and the cause quickly found donations by the hundreds, pouring generously from the students and the college faculty. The movement was a grand success for all those involved and the key to the well-built house was gifted to the family of the concerned student. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The post Sahapadikkoru Veedu 🏠: CEC Flood Relief Activity appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post IGNITE-2012 appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The most remarkable event in the history of CEC is none other than the arrival of Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam. Whenever we hear that name, an indomitable spirit will burn within us to catch the dreams breaking the shackles of obstacles. CECians were in enthusiasm to welcome the one who has the calibre to ignite our minds and faculty to enrich our soul. It was on November 26, 2012 that the Missile Man of India, Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam visited College of Engineering Chengannur for the IGNITE Annual Meet hosted by IEEE Student Branch College of Engineering Chengannur. IGNITE covered around 13 districts of Kerala, travelling the length and breadth of Kerala. Integrated Guidance Network of IEEE",
