  {
    "id": "cceb8212b9281b18",
    "source": "page",
    "url": "https://ceconline.edu/feed",
    "title": "College of Engineering Chengannur",
    "section": "MAKER STATION",
    "text": "APJ Abdul Kalam. Whenever we hear that name, an indomitable spirit will burn within us to catch the dreams breaking the shackles of obstacles. CECians were in enthusiasm to welcome the one who has the calibre to ignite our minds and faculty to enrich our soul. It was on November 26, 2012 that the Missile Man of India, Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam visited College of Engineering Chengannur for the IGNITE Annual Meet hosted by IEEE Student Branch College of Engineering Chengannur. IGNITE covered around 13 districts of Kerala, travelling the length and breadth of Kerala. Integrated Guidance Network of IEEE of Technical Education (IGNITE) – a wakening journey full of life, ideas and innovations to identify young talents across Kerala, constitute these students into a network and reinforce the research backbone of the society with these little masterminds. About hundreds gathered at CEC’s auditorium to celebrate the event. The presence of other dignitaries such as Dr. Jyothiraj V.P (Former Principal of CEC), Mr. Sayeed Rasheed (Director, IHRD), V.P Devassia (Additional Director and formal Principal ,CEC), P.C Vishnunath (MLA Chengannur), Mr. Sathish Babu and Smt. Suja John (Chairperson, Chengannur Municipality) added elegance to the dias. The events started with a prayer and a moment of silence in memory of 26/11 victims. The ceremony was presided by our former President Kalam who himself addressed the gathering and won the hearts of many with his eloquent delivery – an amalgam of experiences and his vision for India. After an hour long speech, he closed with his message that we must be remembered for creating our own page in the book of history. He persuaded students to think out of box and to follow their dreams. He added the significance of engineering and technology in this contemporary era and asked the students to take an oath. He made the gathering repeat after him as he recited the poem: “I am born with potential I am born with goodness and trust I am born with ideas and dreams I am born with greatness I am born with confidence I am born with wings So, I am not meant for crawling, I have wings, I will fly I will fly and fly.” The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The NSS units of the College of Engineering Chengannur conducted an orientation programme for the interested first years students of the college. The post IGNITE-2012 appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post Corona Battalion: Student curates a system to aid the fight against the virus appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . With the covid-19 virus gripping the nation tighter day by day, Aswin Mohan, a 4th-year student of CEC took the challenge of developing a fully-fledged system for officials and organizations to track virus cases and keep tabs on those under inspection. The system which alleviates the pressure on health officials was swiftly adopted by the government to aid in its fight against the virus. Being added with novel features each development cycle, the rapid production of the system stands as a testament to the standard of the technical armada of the college. The post Corona Battalion: Student curates a system to aid the fight against the virus appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . The post SUMMIT’19, the biennial techno-cultural fest of College of Engineering Chengannur appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur . With an aroma of indispensable positivity and ceremonious gratitude, CEC opened itself to the grandeur of its maiden techno-cultural fiesta: SUMMIT, on the 29th, 30th, and 31st of March 2019. The relentless 3-day techno and cultural euphoria was an adventurous ride from seminars and workshops to contests, making its journey through treasure hunts, live gaming, coding and much more exciting and ingenious ideas. SUMMIT is a platform for demonstrating technical ingenuity and artistic aptitude that rightfully attracts students from various colleges to compete on a big scale. The post SUMMIT’19, the biennial techno-cultural fest of College of Engineering Chengannur appeared first on College of Engineering Chengannur .",
