  {
    "id": "6c1d365d60919a58",
    "source": "page",
    "url": "https://ceconline.edu/organizations",
    "title": "Organizations - College of Engineering Chengannur",
    "section": "Training & Placement Cell (TPC)",
    "text": "With the aim of instilling technical competence and responsibilities in budding engineers, IEEE Student Branch College of Engineering Chengannur was established in 1997. Since then it has developed into one of the premier student branches in the state. The institute has received global acclaim due to its numerous contributions to the society and vibrant volunteers. It currently functions with five student branch chapters along with a Special Interest Group on Humanitarian Technology and a Women in Engineering Affinity Group which is among the first of its kind within the Asia Pacific region. College of Engineering Chengannur has initiated its NCC unit under the NAVAL wing of the Armed Forces. The unit is commissioned on 16th October 2014 with a total strength of 50 cadets. There will be 33% of seats are reserved for lady cadets. Our NAVY NCC unit functions under 3(K) Navy Unit Kollam, of the Kollam group NCC headquarters. The National Service Scheme CEC comprising 3 Units and around 300 volunteers, plays a major role in molding them as ‘Social Engineers’ and inculcating values like compassion and benevolence in them. The enthusiasm and dedication of all the volunteers combined with the faculty support make each program successful. TinkerHub CEC is a Campus Community initiative of TinkerHub Foundation at College Of Engineering Chengannur. We at TinkerHub CE Chengannur, aim to fulfill the mission and vision of Tinkerhub Foundation at our campus by empowering students with access to the knowledge they need to thrive in the new world. TinkerHub Campus Community is for students who want to learn and teach technology. We want our community members to understand and embrace the power of critical thinking, problem-solving, innovation, and entrepreneurship. Electronics Students Society (ExESS) is a technical forum for students in the electronics department of College of Engineering Chengannur.The primary goal of ExESS is to explore and strengthen the technical knowledge and practical skills of our students and make them industry-ready . We also intend to highlight what’s new and coming in the realm of electronics to help students comprehend technology and push it beyond what the world has seen. ExESS arranges a variety of activities for students throughout the year. Its Workshops to gain hand on experience, Hackathon for practical problem solving, and Quiz programmes were marked by active participation of our students.Webinar series on some of the most relevant topics by eminent personnels were also conducted. Product Design and Development Center (PRODDEC) is a common platform for all CECians. It was the first technical forum in CEC formed in 1996 with the vision of integrating technical ideas and to develop products with engineering outlook. The executive council of PRODDEC is always in search of new avenues to help and encourage the students, to put their theoretical knowledge to practical use. FOCES is an organization of CSE students of the college. The forum aims at improving the technical and industrial knowledge of the students and strives to keep them abreast of the latest software and technologies evolving in the information technology field. It welcomes the freshers into computer engineering by conducting introductory orientation classes. It organizes talks by eminent personalities in the industry on evolving technologies in computing, workshops on the latest developing platforms, languages, and software packages in the IT industry, and helps coordinate and implement software projects for the students in the Computer Science & Engineering Dept. Started in 2012, the Electrical Engineering students association, SURGE is committed to enhancing the skills of electrical students by organizing technical seminars, workshops, training programs, and industrial visits.SURGE aims at increasing the technical knowledge of the students on the basic concepts of electricity. Modern-day technology and its applications at the industry level, thereby enhancing a professional touch to their thoughts. Department of Industries & Commerce, Government of Kerala formulated a scheme to set up Entrepreneurship Development Clubs in colleges of the State to inculcate Entrepreneurial Culture amongst youth and equip them with the skills, techniques, and confidence to act as torch-bearers of Enterprise for the new generation. The objectives of the Entrepreneurship Development Club are to infuse entrepreneurship qualities, sensitize the industrial scenario of the state, nurture the latent entrepreneurial talent, develop awareness among its members of the attitudes, values, and skills of successful entrepreneurs around the globe, etc. The Innovation and Entrepreneurship Development Cell [IEDC] Bootcamp College of Engineering Chengannur came into existence in June 2015 with the notion of molding youngsters into technological entrepreneurs and innovative leaders. The cell act as an instigator in nurturing entrepreneurship and developing & cherishing a spirit of innovation and a prompt to follow their passion amongst the student community of CEC in association with KSUM. We envision boosting innovative thinking and becoming a facilitator between the students inside the campus and the industry. Platform to nurture and develop, performance and other artistic expressionism",
