  {
    "id": "2c2ee4fbd05bde0b",
    "source": "page",
    "url": "https://ceconline.edu/organizations",
    "title": "Organizations - College of Engineering Chengannur",
    "section": "Training & Placement Cell (TPC)",
    "text": "skills of successful entrepreneurs around the globe, etc. The Innovation and Entrepreneurship Development Cell [IEDC] Bootcamp College of Engineering Chengannur came into existence in June 2015 with the notion of molding youngsters into technological entrepreneurs and innovative leaders. The cell act as an instigator in nurturing entrepreneurship and developing & cherishing a spirit of innovation and a prompt to follow their passion amongst the student community of CEC in association with KSUM. We envision boosting innovative thinking and becoming a facilitator between the students inside the campus and the industry. Platform to nurture and develop, performance and other artistic expressionism for students of college. 3 days long annual cultural fest followed by 6 days of auditions and offstage events is the key event of the forum. For the enthusiastic sports lovers of our college, we conduct an annual sports week in our college which involves both track and field events along with indoor games such as Chess and Carroms. Apart from the annual meet, there are special annual inter-semester Football Competition (Tiger 5), Badminton Competition (Smash), Throwball Competition for girls, and an Inter-Collegiate Volleyball Championship (I Shall). Aims to introduce students to the various aspects of entertainment medium, cinema, and focus on informal gatherings where themes, experiences, and emotions that form part of our lives are discussed. A platform for students to explore the world of cinema as an educational, cultural, and artistic expression. Amidst the typical flutter of academic and professional activities, music calls to those who listen. Where music meets the mind, The Chosen is the official band of CEC composed of students with a strong inclination to the musical arts. KDC, The official dance club of CEC. An extracurricular club that brings together students who have interest and talent for dance, giving them new exciting opportunities to nurture, bring out and showcase their inner dancer! The Alumni Relations Cell of the College of Engineering Chengannur consists of a Faculty in charge, students, and Alumni members. The main objective of the cell is to maintain a constant friendly relationship with all the alumni members of the college. This includes Inviting the Alumni members to various college events and making arrangements for the visit of alumni members to the college. The cell also initiates to build a database of the entire pass-out students along with annual alumni meetings. The Training and Placement Cell (TPC) College of Engineering Chengannur is an integral part of the Institution. It is a body of active students, guided by Staff-in-Charge. The placement cell activities include coordinating pre-placement talks, and organizing drives throughout the academic year both in the college and the local area. The Cell’s primary objective is to provide training and placements to college students. Students are led to take the initiative to develop their attitude in the workplace, and soft skills and are allowed to develop technical skills alongside analytical capabilities.",
