    "section": "page 14",
    "text": "2.2 Categorization of Seats in Self-Financing/Autonomous Institutions: The categorization of seats in Self-financing Colleges run by institutions under Govt. Control, Govt. Cost Sharing Colleges and other Private Self- financing/ Autonomous colleges will be notified separately. As per the orders of the Hon’ble Supreme Court of India dated: 09.05.2017 on WP(C) No. 267/2017, the allotments/admissions to the State Quota seats in all the Government as well as Private Self Financing Medical and Dental colleges shall be done through a Common Counselling to be conducted by the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations. The Common Counselling will include NRI seats in Self Financing Medical & Dental Colleges and Minority Community Quota seats in Private Self Financing Medical & Dental Colleges having Minority Status. As per NCISM directives, the allotment to the state quota seats (including Management/NRI/Minority seats, if any) in Private Self Financing Ayurveda/ Siddha/Unani colleges shall be done through a common counselling, to be conducted by the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations. The All India Merit seats in Private Self Financing Medical/ Dental/ Ayurveda/ Siddha/Unani colleges are also included in the Centralized Allotment Process conducted by the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations. Note: Autonomous Colleges are the colleges, affiliated to the University conferred with Autonomous status by the University Grants Commission and notified as such by University. The academics and examination Regulations applicable to Autonomous Colleges shall be governed by the regulations /Orders /Circulars issued by the University from time to time, as applicable to Autonomous Colleges. Candidates applied for admission in Autonomous Engineering Colleges shall verify those regulations and satisfy themselves before applying for it. 2.3 Engineering Courses: 2.3.1 The B.Tech. Degree courses affiliated to various Universities in Kerala including Autonomous Colleges, under the semester scheme of studies comprise eight semesters. 2.3.2 The B.Tech. (Agricultural Engineering) and the B.Tech. (Food Technology) courses under the Kerala Agricultural University [KAU]. 2.3.3 The B.Tech. (Dairy Technology) and B.Tech (Food Technology) courses under the Kerala Veterinary and Animal Sciences University [KVASU]. 14 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
