    "section": "page 23",
    "text": "NEET-UG 2025 prepared by CEE as stipulated in pre-para will be considered while preparing the inter-se merit list for admission to MBBS, BDS, BAMS, BHMS, Agriculture, Forestry, Co-operation & Banking,Veterinary & Fisheries courses. (ii) All the candidates seeking admission under the ‘Special Reservation Categories’ will have to appear for the Entrance Examination concerned and find place in the respective rank list. In case the admissions are based on inter-se merit lists, only those candidates who have been included in the respective rank lists will be considered for preparing the inter-se merit list. (iii) Candidates should mention the item of reservation claimed in the relevant columns in the application and should be otherwise eligible as per Clause 6. (iv) Candidates should upload required certificates in the prescribed format to the online application within the stipulated time, as mentioned for each item, in support of the claim from Clauses 5.2.1 to 5.2.15. (v) Selection to the seats mentioned from Clause 5.2.1 to 5.2.14 will be made on the basis of rank in the respective rank list. Selection to the seats mentioned from 5.2.15 to 5.2.17 (except 5.2.15(iii)), will be made on the basis of the inter-se merit of the candidates in the merit list prepared for the purpose. For special reservations mentioned from Clause5.2.15 to 5.2.17 (except 5.2.15(iii)), only those candidates who are included in the respective rank list will be considered for inclusion in the inter-se merit list. (vi) In cases where candidates are to be allotted to the ‘Special Reservation’ seats of Engineering/ Architecture/ B.Pharm/ Medical/ Agriculture/ Veterinary/ Fisheries courses on thebasis of inter-se merit list, the authorities concerned will forward the preliminary merit list of candidates prepared on the basis of the proficiency of the candidate in the respective fields to the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations. Such preliminary proficiency list should reach the Office of the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations on or before 30thApril 2025. Lists received after this date will not be entertained under any circumstance and such seats will be merged to the Mandatory reservation quota. (vii) Seats under Special Reservation in Self-financing colleges, if available, will be notified separately. Such seats, if any, will not be shifted to Government/Aided colleges under any circumstance. The details of Special Reservation seats earmarked in Govt./Aided Colleges are given in Annexure II (2) (a), III (2), IV (2), V (2), VI (3)(a) and VII (4). 5.2.1 Ex-servicemen Quota (XS): Applicants to this category should invariably upload to the online application, a certificate in Annexure XIII (a)(i) or 23 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
