ian should not be more than Rs.12000/- per annum. The Agricultural income and non-agricultural income of the parent/guardian of the applicant should specifically be mentioned in the income certificate issued by the competent authority not below the rank of Village Officer of the Revenue Department in the prescribed format in Annexure XVI (a) to be uploaded to the online application for KEAM-2025 (Refer Annexure VII (4). Eleven Seats are reserved for Open quota (CA), and three seats each are reserved for SC/ST (CS) and SEBC (CE) under this category. If no suitable candidate is available in SC/ST or SEBC, the vacant seats will be filled 28 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
