    "text": "5.2.14 Scouts and Guides for Engineering Courses (SG): Two seats are reserved for Rashtrapathi Scouts and Guides for Engineering Courses. Candidates seeking reservation under this quota should upload the Rashtrapathi Guide Certificate signed by the President of India to the online application. In the absence of this Certificate, Specimen Certificate signed by the Director of General Education (DGE), Kerala and the State Secretary, Kerala State Bharat Scouts and Guides, will be considered (see Annexure II(2) (a). 5.2.15(i) Agricultural Assistants (AG)/ VHSE (Agri.) Holders (VA)/ Diploma Holders in Agricultural Science (DG)/Diploma in Organic Agriculture (DN) [For Agricultural courses only]: Candidates, who claim the seats reserved for Agricultural Assistants should obtain a service certificate in the prescribed format in Annexure XIV (b) from the Head of Office concerned. They have to send a printout of the Application Acknowledgement Page along with the service certificate and attested copies of all certificates to the Registrar, Kerala Agricultural University, Main Campus, Vellanikkara, Thrissur-680656, on or before 30th April 2025. Candidates who claim the seats reserved for Agricultural Assistants shall produce their relieving certificate on the date of admission. The allotment of the seats reserved for Agricultural Assistants should be based on an Entrance Exam conducted by the Kerala Agricultural University. If there are no candidates to that seat, the seat should be reverted to Mandatory quota. Candidates who claim the seats reserved for Diploma holders in Agricultural Science (DG)/ Diploma in Organic Agriculture (DN)/ VHSE (Agri.) holders (VA) shall upload the Diploma certificate in Agricultural Science/Diploma certificate in Organic Agriculture/VHSE (Agri.) certificate with the online application. Final year VHSE (Agri) students/HSE (Gardener, Floriculturist (including Floriculturist Open Cultivation and Floriculturist Protected Cultivation), Micro Irrigation Technician, Organic Grower, Vegetable Grower, Agriculture Extension Service Provider, Interior Landscaper courses - as per NSQF stream) students can also claim the seats reserved for VHSE (Agri.) Holders and such candidates should upload respective course certificates with the online application. Such candidates shall produce their pass certificate on the date of admission. The allotment to the seats reserved for Diploma holders in Agricultural Science (DG)/Diploma in Organic Agriculture (DN)/VHSE (Agri.) holders/Final year VHSE (Agri.)/HSE (Gardener, Floriculturist (including Floriculturist Open Cultivation and Floriculturist Protected Cultivation), Micro Irrigation Technician, Organic Grower, Vegetable Grower, Agriculture Extension Service Provider, Interior Land scaper) students (VA) shall be based on the 30 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
