    "text": "Director of Medical Education will inform the CEE of such seats before the Third Round Allotment conducted by the CEE. 5.5.9 The seats unavailed by the EWS category candidates will be allotted under State Merit, as a general rule. However, in the case of courses for which EWS reservation is implemented using supernumerary seats sanctioned by the respective Central Regulatory Bodies/Universities, the rules prescribed by the seat sanctioning authority have to be followed in deciding the convertibility of EWS seats. 5.5.10 The conversion of unallotted minority and NRI quota seats in self-financing colleges for MBBS/BDS courses will be carried out as per G.O (Rt)No.1517/2022/ H&FWD, dated. 25.06.2022. The NRI/Minority seat conversion algorithm will be as follows. No Conversion Category converted to Category 1 NRI - Minority NRI open 2 NRI - Open State Merit (SM) 3 Minority State Merit (SM) The unallotted Management quota seats in Aided/Self-financing Ayush colleges will be converted to state merit seats. 5.5.11 Conversion of unavailed category seats will be carried out as per the respective prospectus clauses during the third phase of the centralised allotment process for the respective courses as per the schedule fixed by the central councils concerned. Category conversions will be carried out only when the options of eligible candidates belonging to the particular conversion category registered for the centralized allotment process have been exhausted. 5.6 Candidates seeking admission in minority quota seats (Christian/Muslim) available in Self-financing Colleges with Minority status should upload Community certificate/Minority Certificate obtained from the Village Officer concerned (See Annexures XXXIII and XXVIII for format). If religion is correctly recorded in SSLC/Educational Certificate of the candidate it can be considered instead of the Community/Minority Certificate issued by the Village Officer. However, candidates belonging to the minority (Christian/Muslim) communities who are entitled to a Non-Creamy Layer certificate for the SEBC reservation in the state for educational purpose can 44 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
