lifying examination within the stipulated time, as per the notification of CEE. 6.2.7 Candidates referred to in Note to Clause 6.2.1 who have only appeared or are appearing for the BSc. Degree Examination, are not eligible to apply as per Clause 6.2.6. 6.2.8 No rounding off of the percentage of marks to the nearest whole number is permitted. For example, a score of 50 marks out of 100 or 150 marks out of 300 alone will be considered as 50% marks and scores of 45 53 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
