    "section": "page 61",
    "text": "6. The candidate shall produce the sworn affidavit from the Sponsor in a stamp paper worth Rs. 200/-. The same shall also be notarized by the Notary Public, disclosing that the student is dependent of the sponsor and all expenses i.e. tuition fee and special fee, of the candidate for the entire course period will be borne by the Sponsor. 7.7 (i) Those seeking admission to Medical courses as per Clause 6.2.1 should satisfy the academic eligibility conditions at the time of submission of application. (ii) All Candidates who have passed/are appearing for the Higher Secondary or equivalent examination will be provisionally permitted to apply for admission under Medical & Medical Allied courses including MBBS/BDS, if they otherwise satisfy the eligibility conditions. They should produce the original mark list of the qualifying examination passed, at the time of admission. Supreme Court of India in SLP(c) No.21720/2018 Dated: 27.02.2024 has declared that students from open schools recognized by the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) and State Boards are eligible to participate in the NEET. As per NEET (UG) information bulletin 2025, the candidatures of candidates in the NEET (UG) – 2025 who have passed the qualifying examinations i.e. class 12 from National Institute of Open Schooling or State Open Schools or as private candidates from recognized State Boards; or with Biology/Biotechnology as an additional subject shall be allowed, but Subject to the outcome of Special Leave Petitions/Appeals filed by National Medical Commission. (iii) Those candidates, who have passed the qualifying examinations i.e. 10+2 from other than that of CBSE, ICSE, Kerala Board of Higher Secondary examinations shall produce eligibility certificate from the Kerala University of Health Sciences (KUHS) at the time of admission in an institution affiliated under KUHS. Candidates are required to visit University website www.kuhs.ac.in’ for more details. (iv) All Candidates who have passed/are appearing for the Higher Secondary or equivalent examination will be provisionally admitted to the Engineering Entrance Examination under KEAM-2025, if they otherwise satisfy the eligibility conditions. All candidates should verify and submit marks online through Official website of CEE for Engineering Courses and those who have disputes on the marks which is shown in the candidate portal should upload the mark list of the qualifying examination, on or before the date prescribed by the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations through notifications. All candidates should 61 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
