    "section": "page 63",
    "text": "Note: In addition, examination centres at Chennai, Hyderabad, Bengaluru and Bahrain are under consideration.The examinations at these centres will be conducted only if minimum numbers of applications are received for the respective centres. Otherwise, the centre allotment will be based on the subsequent preferences of the candidate. 9.1.1No request for change in the Examination centre will be entertained. 9.2 Papers/Subjects in the Entrance Examinations: G.O.(Ms) No.153/99/H.Edn. Dated 22.11.1999 stipulates that the Entrance Examination for engineering courses will be conducted with a relative weightage of 5:3:2 in Mathematics, Physics & Chemistry. Candidates applying for admission to Medical & Medical Allied Courses shall have to appear for NEET-UG 2025 and have to qualify as per the qualifying criteria mentioned in 9.7.5 (ii) and 9.7.5 (iii). The Entrance Examination for Pharmacy course will be conducted with a relative weightage of 3:2 in Chemistry & Physics. Candidates applying for admission to B.Pharm Course shall have to appear for Kerala Pharmacy Entrance Examination and qualify as per the qualifying criteria mentioned in clause 9.7.5(v) of the prospectus. 9.2.1 SUBJECTS: (a) Subjects for the Engineering Entrance Examination: Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry (b) Subjects for the Pharmacy Examination Chemistry, Physics 9.2.2 Candidates desirous of being considered for any of the Medical & Medical Allied courses will have to write NEET-UG 2025 conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA). 9.2.3 Candidates who wish to be considered ONLY for Engineering Courses [including B.Tech. (Agri. Engg.), B.Tech. (Food Tech.) courses under the Kerala Agricultural University, B. Tech. (Dairy Technology) and B.Tech (Food Technology) courses under Kerala Veterinary and Animal Sciences University and B.Tech (Food Technology) course under Kerala University of Fisheries and Ocean Studies, [offered by KAU/KVASU/KUFOS] will have to appear and qualify Engineering Entrance Examination 9.2.4 Candidates desirous of being considered for Architecture course should appear for the ‘National Aptitude Test in Architecture’ (NATA) to be conducted by the Council of Architecture, India and the candidates are advised to qualify in NATA-2025 as per the guidelines and schedule published by the Council of Architecture (CoA). Candidates included in the Engineering rank list will 63 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
