    "section": "page 72",
    "text": "(c) Rank list for admission to B. Arch Course will be prepared by giving equal weightage to the score obtained in the ‘National Aptitude Test in Architecture’ (NATA) and to the marks/grades obtained in the Qualifying Examination by the candidate (As per guidelines of the Council of Architecture, India). Marks obtained by the candidate in the National Aptitude Test in Architecture (NATA) out of 200 will be added to the total marks/*grades secured by the candidate in the Qualifying Examination computed out of 200. The Rank list will be prepared based on the total marks obtained out of 400, computed as above (* If grades are awarded to candidates in their Qualifying Examination, it will be converted to equivalent marks for this purpose). Candidates to be considered for inclusion in the rank list for allotment to B. Arch course in all institutions including private Self-financing Colleges have to appear for ‘NATA’ and secure minimum score as prescribed by CoA. [Refer Clause 6.2.3 (b)] (d) (i) Rank list for Medical Courses (MBBS/BDS/BHMS/BSMS/BUMS Courses) except BAMS will be prepared on the basis of rank obtained in NEET-UG 2025 subject to the Nativity conditions as in Clause 6.1 and also subject to the qualifying criteria as per Clause 9.7.5(ii). (ii) Rank list for Medical Allied Courses (Agriculture, B.Sc.(Hons)Co- operation & Banking/B.Sc (Hons) Agri Business Management, Climate Change & Environmental Science, B.Tech Biotechnology (under KAU),Veterinary, Forestry and Fisheries courses) will be prepared on the basis of rank obtained in NEET-UG 2025 subject to satisfying the Nativity conditions as in Clause 6.1 and also subject to the qualifying criteria as per Clause 9.7.5(iii). (e) Rank List for Ayurveda Course: A separaterank list for Ayurveda Course will be prepared based on the score obtained in NEET-UG 2025 subject to the Nativity conditions as in Clause 6.1 and also subject to the qualifying criteria as per Clause 9.7.5(ii). For candidates who have taken Sanskrit as their second language in Higher Secondary or equivalent examination, additional 8 marks will be added to the total marks secured by them in the NEET-UG 2025 for the preparation of Ayurveda rank list. Such candidates should upload course certificate to the online application. For others, the total marks in the NEET- UG 2025 alone will be considered. Candidate should verify/submit the NEET UG Score 2025 through the official website of Commissioner for Entrance Examinations for the preparation of Medical & Medical Allied Courses & Ayurveda Rank List within the date specified in the Notifications issued for this purpose by the CEE. 72 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
