    "id": "4cee492c4824942c",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://cee.kerala.gov.in/keam2025/pdf/Prospectus.pdf",
    "title": "Microsoft Word - KEAM Prospectus 2025-Secretariate-Final-14.02.25",
    "section": "page 76",
    "text": "Detailed notification in this regard will be issued by the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations, in due course. The marks of the qualifying examination and NATA’ score received on or before 30-06-2025 alone will be considered for preparing the Architecture Rank list. The rank list so published will be final and the marks received subsequently will not be considered under any circumstances. The Commissioner for Entrance Examinations will not be responsible for any delay in the publication of the result of the qualifying examination or NATA. 9.7.10 (a)Validity of the rank lists published by the CEE: The rank list of Engineering, Architecture, B.Pharm, Medical & Medical Allied Courses (MBBS/ BDS/ BHMS/ BSMS/ BUMS/ Agriculture/ Forestry/ Veterinary /B.Sc.(Hons)Co-operation & Banking/B.Sc (Hons) Agri Business Management/ Climate Change & Environmental Science/ B.Tech Biotechnology (under KAU)/ Fisheries) and BAMS courses will be valid till the closing date of admission as prescribed by the Hon’ble Supreme Court/Central councils /Universities concerned. (b) Weeding out Rule: The records of KEAM 2025 will be preserved only till 31st March 2026. 9.7.11 Publication of Provisional Category Lists: (a) Separate provisional category lists will be published for Community reservation, Special reservation, Persons with Disabilities, and EWS reservation. (b) There will be separate category lists based on Engineering, Architecture, B.Pharm, Medical (MBBS/BDS/BHMS/BSMS/BUMS), BAMS and Medical Allied courses (Agriculture/Veterinary/Forestry/B.Sc.(Hons)Co- operation & Banking/B.Sc (Hons) Agri Business Management, Climate Change & Environmental Science, B.Tech Biotechnology (under KAU),Fisheries) rank lists. Candidates are advised to verify the various merit/category lists published by the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations, and satisfy themselves regarding their position in the list, such as, inclusion under different categories, eligibility for communal/special reservation, etc. Complaints, if any, in this regard may be sent to the Office of the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations, within the stipulated time notified by the CEE. Final Category list will be published after considering the objections/complaints, filed by the candidates. Complaints received thereafter will not be entertained under any circumstances. 76 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
