    "id": "862c1642bb189f60",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://cee.kerala.gov.in/keam2025/pdf/Prospectus.pdf",
    "title": "Microsoft Word - KEAM Prospectus 2025-Secretariate-Final-14.02.25",
    "section": "page 84",
    "text": "11.3 (a) Seats for the Engineering, Architecture, B.Pharm, MBBS, BDS, Ayurveda, Homoeo, Siddha, Unani courses and seats for the Agriculture, Forestry, B.Sc.(Hons)Co-operation & Banking/B.Sc (Hons) Agri Business Management, Climate Change & Environmental Science, B.Tech Biotechnology (under KAU), Agricultural Engineering and Food Technology Courses under the Kerala Agricultural University, Fisheries and Food Technology course under Kerala University of Fisheries & Ocean Studies, and BVSc & AH, Dairy Technology and Food Technology courses under Kerala Veterinary & Animal Sciences University will be available for allotments by CEE through the CAP. (b) The courses for Option Registration under CAP are classified as Engineering Stream, Architecture Stream, Medical Stream, Medical Allied Stream and Pharmacy Stream. All courses listed in Clauses 1.3.1 and 1.3.2 are included in Engineering Stream and Architecture Stream respectively. All courses listed in Clauses 1.3.3, 1.3.4, 1.3.5 and 1.3.6 are included in Medical Stream. B.Pharm course under clause 1.3.7 is included in Pharmacy Stream. (c) The candidates are eligible to register option to the courses of any stream or all streams provided they are qualified with a rank in the respective rank lists of KEAM-2025 as per the conditions specified in Clauses 5, 6 and 9 of the KEAM-2025 Prospectus. (d) Only female candidates can register options to the courses in Women’s Colleges under CAP if they are otherwise qualified as per various Clauses of the KEAM-2025 Prospectus. 11.4 Rules and regulations governing allotments through submission of options: 11.4.1Candidate to register options: Candidates included in the Rank lists for Engineering, Architecture, B.Pharm, Medical & Medical Allied Courses (MBBS/ BDS/ BHMS/ BSMS/ BUMS/ Agriculture/ Forestry/ Veterinary /B.Sc.(Hons)Co-operation & Banking/B.Sc (Hons) Agri Business Management/ Climate Change & Environmental Science/ B.Tech Biotechnology (under KAU)/ Fisheries) and Ayurveda courses 2025, will have to register their options in the stream(s) concerned as prescribed under Clause 11.5, for being considered for allotments to the courses and colleges under the respective stream(s). 11.4.2 Registering Options: Options can be registered only through the website, ‘www.cee.kerala.gov.in’. Candidates will have to register their options in single stream or multiple streams (based on their eligibility) in the ‘Option Registration Page’ accessible through the ‘Candidate Portal’ within the 84 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
