    "text": "course(s) included in that phase, making them unavailable for the subsequent phases. 11.6.8 Allotments as per Guidelines: Allotment to Engineering, Architecture, B.Pharm, MBBS/BDS, BAMS, BHMS, BSMS, BUMS courses will be regulated in conformity with the guidelines of the Central councils concerned (NMC, DCI, AICTE, NCISM,NCH,VCI,ICAR,PCI and CoA). 11.6.9 Centralized Counseling & Stray Vacancy Filling: The Commissioner for Entrance Examinations is authorized to prepare and publish detailed guidelines and conditions for centralizedcounseling and the subsequent stray vacancy filling phases. During further counseling and Stray vacancy filling phases there may be strict constraints on the kinds of moves from one course to another course or from one college to another college. The guidelines will be drafted so as to conform to the corresponding guidelines of the central councils concerned (NMC, DCI, AICTE, NCISM,NCH,VCI,ICAR,PCI and CoA) as far as possible. 11.7 Post Allotment Activities: 11.7.1 Reporting at the College: Candidates who get allotment will have to report before the Principal/Head of the Institution concerned for admission on the dates notified with the following documents: (a) Certificate to prove date of birth. (b) Transfer Certificate from the Institution last attended and Conduct Certificate. (c) Original mark list of the qualifying examination (Higher Secondary or equivalent*) and the Pass certificate of the qualifying examination (if issued). *Candidates seeking admission to B.Tech course under KTU, who have passed a qualifying examination from the examination boards recognized by the Association of Indian Universities (AIU) need not produce equivalency certificate. (d) Eligibility certificate from any University* in Kerala, in the case of candidates who have passed a qualifying examination other than Higher Secondary Examination/Vocational Higher Secondary Examination 93 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
