    "text": "(a) Degree will be awarded only on production of certificate of having successfully completed the prescribed one year internship. (b) Medium of instruction will be English. (c) The total duration for BAMS courses is 4 1/2 years, with three professional courses each of 18 months duration (First professional, Second professional and Third professional). 13.3 Homoeopathy- BHMS Course: The degree will be awarded only after successful completion of one year internship as prescribed by the National Commission for Homoeopathy.  The entire course of BHMS including internship shall be completed within a period of maximum 10 years.  It is mandatory for the interns who have joined internship on or after 29.11.2023 to appear the National Exit Test as per NCH (National Examinations in Homoeopathy) Regulation, 2023. (F.No.3- 104/2023/NCH/HEB/Exam Regulation dated 22.11.2023)  The National Exit Test qualified candidates shall be eligible to get registered as medical practitioners only after completion of remaining duration of rotatory internship and fulfillment of criteria as specified by Board of Ethics & Registration for Homoeopathy.  Each candidate shall be required to undergo compulsory rotatory internship including internship orientation programme within one year from passing of fourth BHMS examination.  Each candidate shall be required to undergo compulsory rotatory internship including internship orientation programme within one year from passing of fourth BHMS examination.  The daily working hours of intern shall be not less than 8 hour.  If there is any delay in the commencement of internship or break during internship due to unavoidable conditions, in such cases, internship period shall be completed within maximum period of twenty four months from the date of passing the qualifying examination of Fourth Final BHMS and in such case the student shall take prior permission from the Head of the Institution in writing with all supporting documents. 103 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
