  {
    "id": "e0117a99fdd9567d",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://cee.kerala.gov.in/keam2025/pdf/Prospectus.pdf",
    "title": "Microsoft Word - KEAM Prospectus 2025-Secretariate-Final-14.02.25",
    "section": "page 233",
    "text": "ANNEXURE – XXIV (iii) CRITERIA FOR ASSESSING THE SUITABILITY OF PwD CANDIDATES FOR ADMISSION TO THE FOLLOWING COURSES A. For B.Sc.(Hon.) Agriculture/B.Sc.(Hon.) Climate Change & Enviornmental Science, B.Tech (Biotech.), B.Sc.(Hons.) B.Sc.(Hons) Co-operation & Banking/B.Sc (Hons) Agri Business Management, B.Tech (Ag.Eng.) and B.Tech (Food Technology) courses Candidates must satisfy the minimum functional requirement as well as the category of benchmark disabilities. They are as follows;  MINIMUM FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENT is S (Sitting), St (Standing), W (Writing), BN (Bending), L (Lifting), MF (Manipulation by Fingers), SE (Seeing), C (Communication) and KC (Kneeling and Crouching).  The SUITABLE CATEGORY OF BENCHMARK DISABILITIES for performing the above-mentioned tasks is as follows: 1. LV (40% - 50%) [Low Vision] 2. HH [Hard of Hearing) 3. LD [Locomotor Disability] including CP [Cerebral Palsy], LC [Leprosy Cured], Dw [Dwarfism], AAV [Acid Attack Victim] and MDy [Muscular Dystrophy] with minimum functional one arm and one leg each: 4. ASD(M) [Autism Spectrum Disorder – Mild], ID (M) [Intellectual Disability- Mild], SLD [Specific Learning Disability]-MI 40% [Mental Illness] 5. MD [Multiple Disabilities] involving above combinations. Only those candidates who satisfy the minimum functional requirement as certified by authorised Medical Practitioner will be considered eligible for admission to the above UG courses. B. For BSc (Hons.) Forestry Course Candidates must satisfy the minimum functional requirement as follows;  MINIMUM FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENT is Bending (BN), Communication (C), Climbing (CL), Crawling (CRL), Hearing (H), Holding (HO), Jumping (Ju), Kneeling & Crouching (KC), Lifting (L), Movement (M), Manipulation by Fingers (MF), Observing (Watching) (O), Picking (P), Pulling and Pushing (PP), Sitting (S), Standing (ST), Writing (W), Reading (R), Walking (W), Seeing (SE), Running, using arms and weapons etc.  The following CATEGORY OF BENCHMARK DISABILITIES are unsuitable for performing the above-mentioned tasks. a) LV (40% - 50%) [Low Vision] b) HH [Hard of Hearing] c) LD [Locomotor Disability] including CP [Cerebral Palsy], LC [Leprosy Cured], Dw [Dwarfism], AAV [Acid Attack Victim] and MDy (Muscular Dystrophy] with minimum functional one arm and one leg each. 233 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "exam",
        "eligibility"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "e2ed10445cedbffc",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://cee.kerala.gov.in/keam2025/pdf/Prospectus.pdf",
    "title": "Microsoft Word - KEAM Prospectus 2025-Secretariate-Final-14.02.25",
    "section": "page 234",
    "text": "d) ASD (M) [Autism Spectrum Disorder – Mild], ID (M) [Intellectual Disability – Mild], SLD [Specific Learning Disability], MI 40% [Mental Illness) e) MD [Multiple Disabilities] involving above combinations. As the B.Sc (Hons.) Forestry course programme requires activities to be performed both indoors and outdoors and requires good hand-eye coordination etc. the mobility of the person should not be restricted. The course also requires involvement in field work/field trips/practical sessions in rougher terrain, remote forest areas which require physical exertion. C. For BVSc & AH Course Candidates must satisfy the minimum functional requirement as well as the category of benchmark disabilities for admission to BVSc. & AH course. They are as follows; As per the notification of Veterinary Council of India dated 08.07.2016 F.No.12-5/2015/VCI Section 7(10), a candidate shall not be allowed admission to Bachelor of Veterinary Sciences and Animal Husbandry Degree Course including those admitted under 15% reserved quota of Veterinary Council of India if he or she suffers the following disabilities, namely:- a. Disability of total body including disability of chest or spine more than 50%. b. Disability of lower limb of more than 50%. c. Disability of upper limb. d. Visually handicapped candidates and those with hearing disability. e. Candidates with progressive diseases like myopathies etc. f. Disabilities which otherwise would interfere in the performance of the duties of a veterinarian. 234 KEAM-2025, © CEE, TVM",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "exam"
      ]
    }
