  {
    "id": "ff22a724c4ea3a23",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ceconline.edu/wpdata/iqac/msecond.pdf",
    "title": "msecond.pdf",
    "section": "page 2",
    "text": "Discussions were made on the following topics : Activities of Industry Institute Interaction Cell(IIIC) and Intellectual Property Right Cell (IPRC)were discussed in detail .The need of industrial training for students in core areas was mentioned. The IIIC member suggested to organize technical talks in Core areas by eminent personalities from Industry. The importance of starting a student chapter of Institution of Engineers in the college was emphasized. The importance of developing student projects for the benefit of society was also stressed. It was also suggested to take up consultancy works/ services by the technical wing of NSS and various professional clubs in the college. All members present were of unanimous opinion that the Mini Fablab has great resources for all these activities. Member from IPR cell suggested to arrange training on IPR for faculty and students. Activity plan of professional bodies for the current semester were discussed. The placement statistics was also presented. Principal congratulated the IEEE student Chapter of the college for the achievements and awards in the year 2019. As per the above discussions, the following decision were taken • It is decided to motivate students to register the Massive Open Online Courses(MOOC) ,NPTEL and other approved online courses. • To conduct demonstration and poster presentation of the final year projects. • It decided to upload the Prequalifier for the EC dept. by the month of June and other departments by the end of this year. • To collect the data base of Alumini with the help of Alumini relation Cell (ARC). • Arrange technical talks by Alumini members working in core areas in Industry and Research Organizations . • Arrange Industrial visits, short term training programmes, for faculty as well as students from first year onwards. • To Start Institution of Engineers Student Chapter at the college • To ensure active participation of technical clubs such as PRODDEC, SURGE etc.in coordinating Techfest as well as student project exhibitions. • To Enhance Utilisation of Mini Fab lab for technical activities. The meeting ended at 4pm. Signature 1. Dr. Jacob Thomas V ,Principal ,CE Chengannur-IQAC Chair person 2. Mr. Bony Thomas ,Scientist E, Electronics Regional Test Laboratory -Member Industry 3. Mr. Biju C Thomas, Chief consultant &Managing Director, Prime builders &Architects, Chengannur 4. Mrs. Deepa A K ,Secretary, WIE Affinity Group IEEE Kerala Section. 5. Mr. Muhammed Rabeeh N, Co-Founder Electree Energy Solutions –Member Alumini 6. Dr. Jyothiraj VP ,HOD EC Department",
