    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 3",
    "text": "I. INTRODUCTION HOME IHRD is an educational agency fully owned and controlled by the Government of Kerala. Since its inception in 1987, IHRD has established 86 institutions across various categories, including nine engineering colleges, to support the development of skilled manpower in fields such as Electronics Engineering, Computer Science and Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Biomedical Engineering, VLSI Design, Cyber Security, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Science, and related areas. All B.Tech courses are affiliated with APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University. Applications are invited online for admission of candidates to B.Tech degree courses (4 years/8 semesters) under NRI quota for the academic year 2025-26 in various engineering colleges under IHRD. Admission to the NRI seats in the engineering courses will be conducted by the respective Principals, who will prepare a rank list based on the applications received in each engineering college. 1",
