  {
    "id": "f4b654e44dba8040",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 8",
    "text": "Refundable Deposit: Rs.1.25 lakhs (to be paid at the time of admission). 2. Candidates admitted under the NRI quota are required to remit the prescribed fee and deposit in the manner and time specified by the Director of IHRD, and the Principal of the engineering college concerned. The refundable deposit collected from NRI students shall IHRD COLLEG FYUGP SEAT Quota Quota be refunded, without interest on completion of 4 years or completion ES DISCIPLI S NE of the course whichever is later. The date of remittance of the deposit at the colleges will be considered for calculating the four year period for the refund eligibility. 3. In addition to para 2 above, candidates will be required to remit the University fees (administration fee, affiliation fee, examination fee, sports arts fee), PTA fee and other fees as instructed by the University or the Principal from time to time. 4. If any student, who gets admission under NRI quota in any one of the engineering colleges under IHRD, decides to discontinue his/her study, he/she will be issued TC only as per the conditions specified in the G.O.(Rt) No.77/2019/ H.Edn dated 18-01-2019. If a student withdraws before the commencement of the course, the entire tuition fee collected from the student will be refunded by the college, after deducting a processing fee of Rs.1,000/ - (Rupees one thousand only). 6",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "fees",
        "exam",
        "facilities",
        "eligibility"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "346455202c6cb330",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 9",
    "text": "If a student leaves after joining the course and if the vacated seat is subsequently filled by another student on or before the last date of admission, the college will refund the tuition fee collected after deducting the processing fee of Rs. 1,000/ - (Rupees One thousand only). Proportionate deductions of monthly fee and hostel rent will also be effected if applicable. University IHRD TOTA In case the vacated seat is not filled, the candidate is eligible to COLLEG FYUGP LSEAT Quota Quota EgSe t the refundable deposit DoISnClIyP.L I All such refunds will be S NE processed only after closure of the admissions. If any candidate who is admitted in the NRI quota subsequently gets admission in the same institution through the counseling process of the Commissioner for Entrance Examinations or through spot admission, the fee paid for NRI quota seats will be adjusted towards the fee to be paid newly, after deducting the admission fee paid for NRI quota seats. 7",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
