  {
    "id": "71c65a316acc0cd3",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 10",
    "text": "IV. ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA FOR ADMISSION HOME University IHRD TOTA 1. NativitCyO:LLEG FYUGP Quota Quota LSEAT ES DISCIPLI S Admission is open to Indian Citizens anNdE Persons of Indian Origin (PIO)/ Overseas Citizens of India (OCI) only. 2. Academic Eligibility: Candidates who have passed Higher Secondary Examination, Kerala or Examinations recognized as equivalent thereof, with atleast 45% marks in Mathematics, Physics & Chemistry put together (or equivalent subjects specified in prospectus of KEAM-2025) are eligible for admission under NRI seats in engineering colleges under IHRD. Candidates belonging to Scheduled Castes (SC) and Scheduled Tribes (ST) need only a pass in the qualifying examination. 3. Age: Applicants must have completed 17 years of age as on 31-12-2025. No relaxation in the minimum age requirement will be granted. 4. Other Eligibility Criteria: The candidates seeking admission to B.Tech NRI seats should be a child/ward/dependent of an NRI and should enclose a declaration from the NRI (form enclosed in section VIII (7)). 8",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "exam",
        "syllabus",
        "eligibility"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "c13d5dbfe78c877d",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 11",
    "text": "V. APPLICATION FORM HOME University TOTA LSEAT S The Application form for admission to B.Tech courses against NRI seats must be completed online through the website, www.ihrdonline.org/ihrdnri or official website of the colleges concerned (Please refer to Section II of this Prospectus for the website address). Separate applications should be submitted for seeking admission to each engineering college under IHRD. The print out of the online application along with required registration fee and documents are to be submitted to the principal of colleges concerned, strictly following the time schedule. 9",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "fees",
        "exam",
        "contact"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "10d21573fa76d58c",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 12",
    "text": "VI. REGISTRATION FEE HOME University IHRD TOTA COLLEG LSEAT Quota Quota ES S The registration fee for all candidates is Rs.1000/-. No fee concession will be allowed to SC/ST/SEBC/OBC candidates. The fee can be paid through the bank account of respective engineering colleges (details available in Section II) or by Demand Draft (DD) drawn on a Nationalized/Scheduled Bank, in favour of the Principal of the engineering college concerned where the applicant desires admission.The DD should be payable at the place of the college. registration fee once remitted shall not be refunded under any circumstances. Applications not accompanied by proof of fee payment will be summarily rejected. 10",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "fees",
        "exam",
        "facilities"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "bb02d90d9bd8748e",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 13",
    "text": "VII. SUBMISSION OF APPLICATION HOME University TOTA LSEAT A print out of the completed online application, along with the proof ofS payment of the registration fee and all required supporting documents, must be submitted to the Principal of engineering colleges concerned (Please refer to section II, for the communication addresses of the engineering colleges) within the stipulated time limit. Applications will be considered only if the applicant has furnished the relevant certificates prescribed in this Prospectus. Under no circumstances will IHRD be responsible for the non-receipt or late receipt of applications. Late applications, incomplete applications, applications not in the prescribed format, or submitted without supporting documents and registration fee will be summarily rejected. 11",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "fees",
        "exam",
        "contact"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "1b45e4912cce4b42",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 14",
    "text": "VIII. DOCUMENTS TO BE SUBMITTED ALONG WITH PRINT OUT OF THE ONLINE APPLICATION HOME 1. Nativity certificate (as per the prospectus conditions issued by the CEE SEAT S for admission to Professional courses, KEAM-2025). 2. Self-attested copy of the SSLC/equivalent certificate to prove the date of birth of the applicant. 3. Self-attested copy of the mark list of the qualifying examination. 4. Self-attested copy of the relevant certificate obtained from competent authority, as prescribed in the KEAM-2025 prospectus and its amendments, to claim relaxation of marks, if applicable (for SC/ST, SEBC and PD candidates only). 5. Details of online payment or Demand Draft for Rs. 1000/- as the registration fee. 6. NRI Certificate: Attested copy of any one of the following documents to prove the current NRI status. (Issued on or after the date of notification for admission to NRI seats 2025-26) Certificate from Bank proving the valid NRE account in the name of the sponsor of the candidate, including his/her current valid full address abroad with phone number (Account statement will not be accepted). Valid Employment Certificate of the sponsor from the firm where he/she is currently employed. Certificate from the Embassy concerned, to prove NRI status. 12",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "fees",
        "exam",
        "contact"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "3caf85615ea931e4",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 15",
    "text": "7. Declaration from the NRI in the prescribed format, as detailed below: I hereby declare that I am a Non Resident Indian and the applicant Mr./Ms. .......................…………………...………………….……is my Son/Daughter/Ward/Dependent coming under the definition of NRI University IHRD TOTA candidate as per section 2(o) of Act XIX of 2006 (Strike out which COLLEG FYUGP LSEAT Quota Quota ES DISCIPLI S NE is not applicable). My Passport No. is …………………… and I am employed/residing at .………………….……………………….…… ………………….…………………………………………………………. …………………………………………………………………………….. ……………... (Fill the details of Foreign Employment/ Place of residence). I hereby undertake to abide by the rules and regulations of IHRD in connection with the admission of the above applicant under NRI seats and I am willing to pay the fees and deposit prescribed for the course. Place : Signature of the Declarant : Date : Name and Full Address abroad : Contact No. : 13",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
