  {
    "id": "35d0f55ff61eed07",
    "source": "pdf",
    "url": "https://ihrd.ac.in/images/stories/admin25/IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "title": "IHRDNRIP25.pdf",
    "section": "page 16",
    "text": "IX. SELECTION AND ADMISSION HOME 1. For the purpose of selection and admission, each college will be treated as a separate unit. Selection/admission to NRI seats in each college will be made by the Principal of concerned engineering college by preparing a rank list from the applications received from the eligible candidates. The admissions will be made strictly on the basis of merit. The rank list will be prepared by observing the following criteria. a.Total of individual percentage of marks obtained for Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry (or equivalent subjects as specified in the KEAM 2025 prospectus) in the final year of the qualifying examination. b.If there is a tie, the percentage of marks for Mathematics, Physics, and Chemistry in the final year will be counted in that order. c.If a tie remains even after the step “b”, total marks in the qualifying examination will be counted. If a tie persists, the age of the candidate will be taken into account and the older candidate will be ranked higher. 2. Merely sending an application does not confer any claim for admission to the applicant. Incomplete applications or those not in the prescribed format will be rejected without any notice. 3. Ragging is a cognizable offense and punishable under provisions of UGC regulations on curbing the menace of ragging in Higher Educational Institutions, 2009. Those who indulge in ragging will be summarily expelled from the educational institution and other legal actions will follow. 14",
    "metadata": {
      "type": "pdf",
      "tags": [
        "admission",
        "courses",
        "exam",
        "syllabus",
        "eligibility"
      ]
    }
  },
