    "text": "DECISIONS AND ACTION TAKEN REPORT- SECOND IQAC MEETING Sl No Decision taken in second IQAC meeting Action taken report 1. It was decided to motivate students to register the Online professional development program Massive Open Online Courses(MOOC) ,NPTEL through Coursera has been started by the college . and other approved online courses. 962 learners have been registered and they have completed 1553 no of courses. 2. To conduct demonstration and poster presentation Posters prepared by final year students (2020 batch ) of the final year projects. were submitted . 3. It decided to upload the Prequalifier for the EC As per the first BoG meeting it has been decided to dept. by the month of June and other departments apply for prequalifier by June 2021. by the end of this year. 4. To collect the data base of Alumini with the help Data base has been collected from 255 Alumini of Alumini relation Cell (ARC). members. 5. Arrange technical talks by Alumini members Technical talks by Alumina working in core areas in Industry and Research Sandeep Balaji Starting UP How to prepare for Organizations. Entrepreneurship Miraj Mohamed Cloud Computing Biju raj Paving path to innovative Projects Nikhil Pattath Gopi (industry) Solar Technology applications; Newer Prospects Mohammed Ajmal C (industry)Bridging Education and Employability 6. Arrange Industrial visits, short term training Faculty have attended Online FDP and training programmes, for faculty as well as students from programs. Students have attended various online first year onwards. internship programs, Final year Electronics students have attended 32 hour of training by experts. 7. To Start Institution of Engineers Student Chapter A Introductory session was conducted by Er. Shaji at the college. Jacob, Chartered Engineer & Chief Academic Coordinator, IEI state centre Committee and student registration process was initiated 8. To ensure active participation of technical clubs PRODDEC:Automatic Hand sanitizer dispensers such as PRODDEC, SURGE etc. in coordinating were developed by students and distributed to Techfest as well as student project exhibitions. schools. An application V-CEC developed and now running in play store. IEDC have developed automatic sanitizers.",
